1
00:00:04,070 --> 00:00:06,650
I'm going to make an absurd suggestion,
but hear me out, okay?

2
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:13,030
Can I have sex with other individuals?

3
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,340
What?

4
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:28,970
You, having sex...

5
00:00:30,620 --> 00:00:32,290
With other men?

6
00:00:32,290 --> 00:00:33,930
Even though we're married?

7
00:00:33,930 --> 00:00:37,600
- What?
- No, let me explain.

8
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:40,210
It's apparently a thing overseas, and...

9
00:00:40,210 --> 00:00:45,060
You must think it's so funny I have ED.

10
00:00:45,060 --> 00:00:48,280
No, not at all.

11
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:50,160
Ouji, please listen to me. I...

12
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:55,960
This is serious to me.
But clearly you don't agree.

13
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:09,730
[Episode 7]

14
00:02:10,790 --> 00:02:14,200
You sure we don't need to report him?

15
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:25,860
It's fine. I won't see him again.

16
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:34,770
I'm partly to blame for aggravating him.

17
00:02:34,770 --> 00:02:39,060
How? You didn't do anything wrong.

18
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:49,280
Help me forget the bad experience.

19
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:57,850
Why don't we stay like this for the night?

20
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,080
I want you to touch me.

21
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:12,160
Please?

22
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:16,840
As you wish.

23
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:32,880
[Ouji]

24
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,900
[Where are you?]
[I'm calling]

25
00:03:37,370 --> 00:03:39,640
He's left me on read.

26
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,400
For two weeks now.

27
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:50,450
Why did I say that?

28
00:03:50,450 --> 00:03:55,120
Why did I think that was such a bright idea?

29
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,330
[Kato Publishing]

30
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:12,140
What's up?

31
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:19,500
One of my steady gigs
is ending our contract this month.

32
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:26,170
They're re-assessing their whole magazine,
or so I was told.

33
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:29,450
I see.

34
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:32,260
Nothing you can do about that.

35
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:33,740
I know.

36
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:40,400
But it's made me face an unfortunate truth.

37
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:45,560
- Huh?
- I now have zero steady gigs.

38
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,770
That's, well...

39
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:55,780
Don't bother cheering me up. I know it's bad.

40
00:04:55,780 --> 00:05:00,630
It's an inevitable for freelancers.

41
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:03,550
But with your reputation,
work will come your way.

42
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:06,710
For now, focus on your one-time gigs, and...

43
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:11,670
Wait... None of those, either?

44
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:15,350
Yeah. I know I'm screwed.

45
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:17,850
I'm practically getting by on part-time jobs.

46
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:21,780
No, not even. I'm not making a single yen.

47
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:24,560
If I'm not a freelancer, what am I?

48
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,550
A vagrant?

49
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:30,540
Oh, I am so screwed...

50
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:34,540
At least your husband will support you!

51
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:38,250
Haru?

52
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:46,220
Okay. Have you ever had a bright idea that,

53
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:50,770
when executing it, didn't go well at all?

54
00:05:50,770 --> 00:05:52,750
- Huh?
- An idea so bright,

55
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:55,500
that it clears up the fog in your brain.

56
00:05:55,500 --> 00:06:00,280
Except, when you put it to action...

57
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:03,250
<i>You must think it's so funny I have ED.</i>

58
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:07,610
Is this about a project of yours?

59
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,460
Yes. You could say that.

60
00:06:11,210 --> 00:06:15,550
It happens all the time with graphic design.

61
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:20,910
Clients will shoot down ideas
I think are great.

62
00:06:20,910 --> 00:06:23,530
I see.

63
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:27,570
Ultimately, it comes down to conversation,

64
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:32,480
and reconciling our ideas
to create the final product.

65
00:06:34,210 --> 00:06:40,060
Reconciling is important, that's for sure.

66
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,740
[Ouji]

67
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:44,800
[Where are you?]
[I'm calling]

68
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:53,020
[Touto Publishing]

69
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:59,940
Do you know Mukai, of Touto Publishing?

70
00:06:59,940 --> 00:07:04,240
She was looking for a new columnist
to write a women's piece.

71
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:08,310
- Really?
- Why not give it a shot?

72
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:10,550
Okay.

73
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:24,680
Aizawa! Long time no see!

74
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,760
Likewise, Ms. Kotani.

75
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:30,820
Sorry, I guess you're an "Ouji" now.

76
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:32,280
Indeed.

77
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:35,240
Congratulations on your marriage.

78
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,810
Thank you.

79
00:07:36,810 --> 00:07:41,170
To think you'd marry him.
The power of a fan is something else.

80
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:43,100
I wouldn't say that.

81
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:45,640
Sensei, the car.

82
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:46,800
Thanks.

83
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,550
"Sensei"?

84
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:52,280
A book I released became a hit,
embarrassing as that is to admit.

85
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,800
I see.

86
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:58,960
I hope you enjoyed the curry.

87
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,360
Huh?

88
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,600
Curry?

89
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:11,180
<i>I saw the recipe on my friend's account.</i>

90
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:19,440
[keiko^kotani]

91
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:43,900
'Sup.

92
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,160
Run away from home?

93
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:49,200
No. Just thought I'd take work seriously.

94
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,060
- Really.
- 'Sup.

95
00:08:51,060 --> 00:08:53,790
- Run away from home?
- I said, no!

96
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:57,090
Why're you so prickly
when the band's back together?

97
00:08:57,090 --> 00:08:58,650
I am not prickly.

98
00:08:58,650 --> 00:09:01,420
Here's a gift to lift your spirits.

99
00:09:01,420 --> 00:09:04,450
- What's this?
- Keiko's new book. I bumped into her,

100
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:08,360
and she gave us each a signed copy.
[I had fun! XXX - Keiko]

101
00:09:11,830 --> 00:09:14,610
What "fun"?

102
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:16,590
You met up with her?

103
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:23,040
He's cheating on you?

104
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:27,370
Hold on. I'm not following.

105
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:32,950
Last I heard, Ouji lacked the drive,
but he hugged you, right?

106
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:38,610
It's not that he lacks it,
it's that he physically can't.

107
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:40,380
Physically can't?

108
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,090
Ah, I see.

109
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:50,180
Which led them to the brink of a divorce.

110
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:54,530
This is too much information to handle.

111
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:57,510
So, why do you suspect him of cheating?

112
00:10:01,380 --> 00:10:03,100
This.

113
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,790
Curry?

114
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:12,070
It's the same exact dish Ouji made for me.

115
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:16,130
Is it?

116
00:10:16,130 --> 00:10:18,380
I mean...

117
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:19,930
Look.

118
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:22,790
"#LeftoversCurry".

119
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:24,910
I can see why that'd get you.

120
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:27,840
Transforming leftovers into a meal?
She's practically showing off.

121
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:31,370
- But...
- See the canned mackerel she used?

122
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:35,170
Maybe?

123
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:38,240
Canned foods aren't "leftovers".

124
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,370
They're made to last decades.

125
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:41,940
Fair point.

126
00:10:41,940 --> 00:10:48,560
It was in our curry, too.
He went and bought a can, for this.

127
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,200
I see.

128
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:54,610
- Even so, that's no reason to...
- Haru.

129
00:10:56,200 --> 00:11:01,150
I might've seen it.

130
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,990
Seen, what?

131
00:11:12,290 --> 00:11:15,160
Sorry, I couldn't find the time to tell you.

132
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:18,530
You can't see their faces.

133
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:21,040
- That's clearly Ouji.
- Maybe, but the woman...

134
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:24,120
- They came out, together!
- She may not be Kotani.

135
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,800
When?

136
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:30,630
About a month ago.

137
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:38,020
- We're taking a quick break.
- Sure.

138
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,540
[Haru: 10 Unread Messages]

139
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:47,370
[Haru: We have to talk]
[I'll be waiting at home]

140
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,170
I'm home.

141
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:06,110
What do you mean, "talk"?

142
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:15,840
Haruchan?

143
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:21,590
Why the nickname?

144
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:25,010
Huh? What are you talking about?

145
00:12:27,010 --> 00:12:32,130
You asked her for the curry recipe.

146
00:12:32,130 --> 00:12:33,800
Curry?

147
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,440
[keiko^kotani]

148
00:12:44,850 --> 00:12:48,090
No, her post coincidentally appeared
on my timeline.

149
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:50,210
I was thinking it looked good,

150
00:12:50,210 --> 00:12:54,450
when she happened to DM me,
so I asked for the recipe.

151
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:58,580
She "happened" to DM you?

152
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,720
Sounds mighty convenient.

153
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,520
What are you...

154
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:07,910
A text from your
longest lasting girlfriend of two years.

155
00:13:07,910 --> 00:13:09,750
What sort of metric is that?

156
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,120
You kept in touch with her?

157
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:14,820
I'm telling you, it was a coincidence.

158
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:18,400
Then was November 13th also a "coincidence"?

159
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,880
What?

160
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:32,240
Why?

161
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,330
No, we weren't...

162
00:13:34,330 --> 00:13:36,790
And where'd you get this photo?

163
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,200
Did you do it with her?

164
00:13:40,850 --> 00:13:43,560
You can't with me, but with your ex?

165
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:47,110
- Like I said...
- Guess I can't beat two years of history.

166
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:49,740
I was only ever a fan in the background.

167
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:51,980
We got married because it was easy for you.

168
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:54,410
- Is that why...
- Knock it off already!

169
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:00,980
You don't trust a thing I said?

170
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:04,020
Well...

171
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:15,710
Fine.

172
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:18,530
Do what you want.

173
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:26,850
Doubt me, have sex with other men. Whatever.

174
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,950
<i>Those eyes.</i>

175
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:35,850
- <i>Ouji...</i>
- <i>You're a bit too persistent.</i>

176
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:40,270
<i>Those cold eyes of his always shut me up.</i>

177
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:43,620
<i>This is serious to me.</i>

178
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:49,400
<i>I'd rather put aside my own desires,
than have this person hate me.</i>

179
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:55,170
NOT!

180
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:00,780
Fine.

181
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:04,560
I will do what I want. Whatever I want.

182
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:28,230
But what is it I want?

183
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:30,540
Did you say something just now?

184
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:38,380
Let's just say being given sudden free reign

185
00:15:38,380 --> 00:15:42,200
is difficult to deal with in its own right.

186
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,250
Your project was approved?

187
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:46,360
Huh?

188
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:49,280
Was this not about your proposal
to Touto Publishing?

189
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,060
I was hoping it went well...

190
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:54,250
Yeah, that's what I was talking about.

191
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:57,790
I'm just... waiting to hear back from them.

192
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:01,190
I'm glad things are going
in a positive direction.

193
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,740
Hello?

194
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:27,150
Sorry I kept you.

195
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:31,030
You don't usually initiate the invite.
What's up?

196
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:35,700
Well, I do feel partly responsible
for what happened, so...

197
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:41,260
You left the house?

198
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:44,550
Yeah. It's been three days since I left,

199
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:47,070
and I've been reading all the manga I want.

200
00:16:47,070 --> 00:16:49,010
You're staying at a manga cafe?

201
00:16:49,010 --> 00:16:51,810
Go to a hotel, you're not a broke student.

202
00:16:51,810 --> 00:16:53,820
Well, I am a vagrant right now.

203
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:55,010
A vagrant?

204
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:57,500
Never mind.

205
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:07,050
Fuyumi says she'll be here soon.

206
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,570
But what about Chizuka?

207
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:11,620
She's apparently making up
for a canceled sleepover.

208
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,580
Sorry I'm late!

209
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:28,900
Fuyumi!

210
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:32,200
- Drunk already?
- Yeah, she's going fast today.

211
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,840
So? What happened?

212
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:40,300
- Your lamb chops. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

213
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,220
I see. Ouji got mad at you.

214
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:45,820
He did! I don't understand why.

215
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:47,530
I'm the one should be mad!

216
00:17:47,530 --> 00:17:49,950
- So you got mad back.
- Yup.

217
00:17:49,950 --> 00:17:54,960
Except, now you don't know what to do.

218
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,650
Why not have sex with another dude?

219
00:17:59,650 --> 00:18:04,770
Ouji gave you his explicit permission.

220
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:10,160
Yeah. But that's only because I asked first.

221
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,580
No, I asked before his affair, not after it!

222
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:16,440
B-Before his affair?

223
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:20,160
So you weren't talking about revenge sex?

224
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:25,540
Ouji said if we couldn't have sex,
then we shouldn't stay together.

225
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:30,140
I want to stay with him.
But never having sex, is a bit...

226
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:32,670
So you suggested other partners?

227
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:37,050
It's apparently a thing overseas,
so I blurted it out.

228
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,830
And how did Ouji react?

229
00:18:38,830 --> 00:18:40,680
- He completely lost his cool.
- I see.

230
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:44,700
Yet he makes his own affair an exception?

231
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,770
That's why I blew a fuse, too.

232
00:18:46,770 --> 00:18:49,100
Make sense.

233
00:18:49,940 --> 00:18:52,940
I'll introduce you to someone.

234
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:55,100
- Huh?
- The perfect man for you.

235
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:57,920
- Akina.
- A professional, with no strings attached.

236
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:00,180
- A professional?
- Oh!

237
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:03,290
The people from the male brothel?

238
00:19:03,290 --> 00:19:05,590
Sorry, who?

239
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:07,780
I guess I haven't told you yet.

240
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:11,760
I'm currently in love with my therapist
from a male brothel.

241
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:17,240
So there are male brothels.

242
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,920
That's the part that shocks you?

243
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:21,940
I'm just a bit overwhelmed with information.

244
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:24,540
How about the three of us all call someone?

245
00:19:24,540 --> 00:19:27,140
They can come chill, nothing steamy involved.

246
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:30,160
Jumping in solo is a bit much for you, right?

247
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:33,450
Yes, but Fuyumi wouldn't...

248
00:19:33,450 --> 00:19:35,710
Married women call on them, too.

249
00:19:35,710 --> 00:19:38,920
- They do?
- Yeah. To alleviate their stress.

250
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:48,560
But you don't have any stress
to alleviate, do you?

251
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:51,040
- My bad.
- Exactly.

252
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:54,180
Fuyumi's the only one of us
leading a respectable, happy lifestyle.

253
00:19:54,180 --> 00:19:56,640
Hey, I lead a respectable lifestyle, too.

254
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:01,460
It's not respectable at all.

255
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:07,100
Ouch, that hurts.

256
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:10,180
- I was referring to myself.
- Huh?

257
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:15,940
My husband only acts like
he understands my work.

258
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:17,970
He harasses me to "do better".

259
00:20:22,550 --> 00:20:23,980
I'm sorry.

260
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,930
Can I fess up about something?

261
00:20:28,190 --> 00:20:34,360
Remember that coworker I mentioned
who was having an affair with an actor?

262
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,020
That was actually me.

263
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:40,410
- What?
- Y-You're so cool!

264
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:42,050
I'm not "cool" at all.

265
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:44,160
Sorry, I couldn't help myself.

266
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:47,940
- How long?
- About half a year now.

267
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:54,630
I spoke big to you, Haru. But the truth is...

268
00:20:54,630 --> 00:21:01,950
<i>First, you have to accept
your true feelings and desires.</i>

269
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:07,970
<i>Don't worry. Accept yourself,
and you'll feel a whole lot better.</i>

270
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:12,500
I was talking about my own experiences.

271
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:17,080
I had no confidence in myself,

272
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:20,980
and would always worry alone.

273
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:28,720
But things became easier
when I began seeing him.

274
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:34,730
It was like I was affirming my own existence.

275
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:38,760
Affirming yourself.

276
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:44,840
But that's no reason to look highly of me.

277
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:48,350
Just the other day, I faced a definite risk.

278
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:52,250
- Did your husband find out?
- No, but it got close.

279
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:57,610
That's the end of my confession.

280
00:21:57,610 --> 00:22:00,110
Aw, I want to hear more!

281
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:01,600
- Next time.
- No, now.

282
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:04,640
We're not here for my story, remember?

283
00:22:07,810 --> 00:22:11,640
So? What'll it be, Haru?

284
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:14,080
Huh?

285
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:19,190
Want to be a bit adventurous?

286
00:22:41,850 --> 00:22:44,880
Akina, actually...

287
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:56,040
Good evening.

288
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,810
We're with the Ebisu Boys Club.

289
00:22:58,810 --> 00:23:00,460
Come on in.

290
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:59,180
<i>My adventure has begun.</i>

291
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:59,000
[Preview]

